# Google Generative AI Configuration
# Required for AI-powered prompt optimization

# Your Google Generative AI API Key
GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Get your free API key from Google AI Studio: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# 3. Replace "your_api_key_here" with your actual API key
# 4. Keep your .env.local file secure and never commit it to version control

# How to get your API key:
# 1. Go to Google AI Studio: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# 2. Sign in with your Google account
# 3. Click "Create API Key" 
# 4. Copy the generated API key
# 5. Paste it above as the value for GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY

# IMPORTANT: After creating your API key, you MUST enable the Generative Language API:
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/generativelanguage.googleapis.com
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Click "Enable" on the Generative Language API
# 4. Wait a few minutes for the API to be activated

# Note: This is a centralized configuration that will be used for all users
# No individual user configuration is required in the application